for 13x18 sheet pan

combine in a cup		
385g warm water		
2g yeast		
		
rest until bubly		
add 10g olive oil		
		
combine in large bowl		
10g salt		
500g flour		
		
add water		
mix until no dry flour remains		
rest 30 minutes		
stretch and fold until smooth		
rest smooth side up in a covered bowl for 8 hours		
form into a cylinder 		
place in oiled pan		
cover 		
refrigerate up to 2 days until 3 hours before baking		
flatten dough 		
place in pan		
flip to cover both sides with oil		
cover 		
rest 1 hour		
stretch to fit pan		
rest 1 hour		
lift to remove air pockets underneath and distribute oil		
make sure to oil sides of the pan		
gently poke dough to the edges of pan to break large bubbles		
rest 30 minutes		
set oven to 500		
rest 30 minutes		
bake 5 minutes		
add sauce		
bake 10-15 minutes		
		
rest 30 minutes before serving		



sauce
heat in medium pot
- 1/2 cup olive oil
add
- 4 minced garlic cloves
cook 2 minutes
add
- 2 tbsp tomato paste
cook until darkened
add
- 2 28 oz can tomatoes ( la san marzano brand  whole tomatoes in tomato purée )
- 1 tbsp sugar
- 2 tsp salt
- 1 tsp balsamic vinegar
- 1/4 tsp crushed pepper
- 1/4 tsp oregano
break open tomatoes
simmer 45 minutes
lightly process with immersion blender

sauce 2
slice in half
- 6 roma tomatoes ( 2.5 lbs )
sprinkle with salt and pepper
drizzle with
- 2 tbsp olive oil
- 1 tsp salt
roast @ 350 for 45 minutes
meanwhile
heat in medium pot
- 6 tbsp olive oil
add
- 4 minced garlic cloves
cook 2 minutes
reserve for later
add to pot
- 1 28 oz can tomatoes ( la san marzano brand  whole tomatoes in tomato purée )
- 1 tbsp sugar
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tsp balsamic vinegar
- 1/4 tsp crushed pepper
- 1/4 tsp oregano
break open tomatoes
simmer 40 minutes
add roasted tomatoes
add garlic oil
simmer 5 minutes
lightly process with immersion blender
